Note:
This file orchestrates the complete monomorphization process.

This file performs the following tasks:
- Process orchestration of monomorphization across entire compilation unit
- Handle generic call site discovery and instantiation requests
- Manage the work queue of pending instantiations
- Process recursive instantiation propagation

This file is essential because of the following reasons:
- Monomorphization enables zero-cost generics by generating specialized code
- Proper orchestration ensures all required instantiations are generated
- Work queue management prevents exponential compilation time

This file consists of the following functions/features/operation types:
- Compilation unit-wide monomorphization driver
- Generic call site analysis and discovery
- Work queue processing for instantiation requests
- Transitive instantiation dependency resolution
:End Note

Note:
========================================
IMPORTS
========================================
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/hashtable.runa" as HashTable
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir.runa" as HIR
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/hir_nodes.runa" as HIRNodes
Import "compiler/middle/transformations/type_instantiation_cache.runa" as Cache
Import "compiler/middle/transformations/generic_instantiation.runa" as GenericInst

Note:
========================================
TYPE DEFINITIONS
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
The MonomorphizationContext manages the entire monomorphization process
for a compilation unit. It maintains:
- The instantiation cache
- Work queue of pending instantiations
- Instantiation context
- Statistics and error tracking

This is the top-level orchestrator that drives monomorphization to completion.

The 200-byte layout provides:
- cache (8 bytes): InstantiationCache pointer
- inst_context (8 bytes): InstantiationContext pointer
- work_queue (8 bytes): Array of pending instantiation requests
- work_queue_capacity (8 bytes): Queue array capacity
- work_queue_size (8 bytes): Current queue size
- work_queue_head (8 bytes): Queue head index
- work_queue_tail (8 bytes): Queue tail index
- processed_count (8 bytes): Number of instantiations processed
- compilation_unit_id (8 bytes): Current CU ID
- instantiated_definitions (8 bytes): List of all instantiated definitions to add to HIR
- call_site_mapping (8 bytes): Hash map from call_site → instantiated_def
- reserved (120 bytes): Future expansion
@End Reasoning

Type called "MonomorphizationContext":
    cache as Integer
    inst_context as Integer
    work_queue as Integer
    work_queue_capacity as Integer
    work_queue_size as Integer
    work_queue_head as Integer
    work_queue_tail as Integer
    processed_count as Integer
    compilation_unit_id as Integer
    reserved_1 as Integer
    reserved_2 as Integer
    reserved_3 as Integer
    reserved_4 as Integer
    reserved_5 as Integer
    reserved_6 as Integer
    reserved_7 as Integer
    reserved_8 as Integer
    reserved_9 as Integer
    reserved_10 as Integer
    reserved_11 as Integer
    reserved_12 as Integer
    reserved_13 as Integer
    reserved_14 as Integer
    reserved_15 as Integer
    reserved_16 as Integer
    reserved_17 as Integer
    reserved_18 as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning
An InstantiationRequest represents a pending generic instantiation that
needs to be processed. The request contains:
- The generic definition to instantiate
- The concrete type arguments
- The call site location (for diagnostics)

Requests are queued as they're discovered during code analysis and processed
in a work queue to handle transitive dependencies.

The 64-byte layout provides:
- generic_def (8 bytes): Pointer to generic HIR definition
- type_args (8 bytes): Pointer to type argument array
- type_arg_count (8 bytes): Number of type arguments
- call_site_location (8 bytes): Source location of call site
- priority (8 bytes): Processing priority (0=normal)
- reserved (24 bytes): Future expansion
@End Reasoning

Type called "InstantiationRequest":
    generic_def as Integer
    type_args as Integer
    type_arg_count as Integer
    call_site_location as Integer
    priority as Integer
    reserved_1 as Integer
    reserved_2 as Integer
    reserved_3 as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning
MonomorphizationStatistics tracks metrics about the monomorphization process
for performance analysis and debugging:
- Number of instantiations generated
- Number of instantiations reused from cache
- Number of work queue iterations
- Peak work queue size

These metrics help optimize compilation performance.

The 64-byte layout provides:
- instantiations_generated (8 bytes): New instantiations created
- cache_hits (8 bytes): Instantiations reused from cache
- work_queue_iterations (8 bytes): Number of queue processing loops
- peak_queue_size (8 bytes): Maximum queue size reached
- total_instantiation_time (8 bytes): Time spent in instantiation (stub)
- reserved (24 bytes): Future expansion
@End Reasoning

Type called "MonomorphizationStatistics":
    instantiations_generated as Integer
    cache_hits as Integer
    work_queue_iterations as Integer
    peak_queue_size as Integer
    total_instantiation_time as Integer
    reserved_1 as Integer
    reserved_2 as Integer
    reserved_3 as Integer
End Type

Note:
========================================
CONTEXT MANAGEMENT
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
Creating the monomorphization context initializes all subsystems:
- Instantiation cache for deduplication
- Instantiation context for generic processing
- Work queue for pending requests

The context is created once per compilation unit and used throughout
monomorphization.
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_monomorphization_context" takes compilation_unit_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate MonomorphizationContext (200 bytes)
    Let ctx_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with 200

    Note: Create instantiation cache
    Let cache be proc cache_create from Cache
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 0, cache

    Note: Create instantiation context
    Let inst_ctx be proc create_instantiation_context from GenericInst with cache, compilation_unit_id
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 8, inst_ctx

    Note: Create work queue (initial capacity 128 requests)
    Let initial_capacity be 128
    Let queue_size be initial_capacity multiplied by 64
    Let work_queue be proc allocate from Layout with queue_size
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 16, work_queue

    Note: Set queue parameters
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 24, initial_capacity
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 32, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 48, 0

    Note: Initialize processed count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 56, 0

    Note: Set compilation unit ID
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 64, compilation_unit_id

    Note: Create list for instantiated definitions
    Let instantiated_defs be proc create from List
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 72, instantiated_defs

    Note: Create hash table for call site mapping (initial capacity 256)
    Let call_site_map be proc hashtable_create from HashTable
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, 80, call_site_map

    Note: Zero remaining reserved fields
    Let reserved_idx be 88
    While reserved_idx is less than 200:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx_ptr, reserved_idx, 0
        Set reserved_idx to reserved_idx plus 8
    End While

    Return ctx_ptr
End Process

@Reasoning
Destroying the monomorphization context cleans up all allocated resources:
- Instantiation cache
- Instantiation context
- Work queue

This is called after monomorphization completes.
@End Reasoning

Process called "destroy_monomorphization_context" takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Destroy instantiation cache
    Let cache be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 0
    If cache is not equal to 0:
        proc cache_destroy from Cache with cache
    End If

    Note: Destroy instantiation context
    Let inst_ctx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 8
    If inst_ctx is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy_instantiation_context from GenericInst with inst_ctx
    End If

    Note: Destroy work queue
    Let work_queue be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 16
    If work_queue is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with work_queue
    End If

    Note: Destroy instantiated definitions list
    Let instantiated_defs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 72
    If instantiated_defs is not equal to 0:
        proc destroy from List with instantiated_defs
    End If

    Note: Destroy call site mapping hash table
    Let call_site_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 80
    If call_site_map is not equal to 0:
        proc hashtable_destroy from HashTable with call_site_map
    End If

    Note: Free context structure
    proc deallocate from Layout with ctx

    Return 1
End Process

Note:
========================================
WORK QUEUE MANAGEMENT
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
Enqueuing an instantiation request adds it to the work queue for processing.
The queue uses a circular buffer for efficient FIFO processing.

When the queue fills, it doubles in capacity to accommodate more requests.
@End Reasoning

Process called "enqueue_instantiation_request" takes ctx as Integer, generic_def as Integer, type_args as Integer, type_arg_count as Integer, call_site as Integer returns Integer:
    Let work_queue be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 16
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 24
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 32
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 40
    Let tail be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 48

    Note: Check if queue is full
    If size is greater than or equal to capacity:
        Note: Grow queue
        proc grow_work_queue with ctx
        Set work_queue to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 16
        Set capacity to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 24
        Set head to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 40
        Set tail to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 48
    End If

    Note: Calculate tail position in queue array
    Let request_offset be tail multiplied by 64
    Let request_ptr be work_queue plus request_offset

    Note: Fill request
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with request_ptr, 0, generic_def
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with request_ptr, 8, type_args
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with request_ptr, 16, type_arg_count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with request_ptr, 24, call_site
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with request_ptr, 32, 0

    Note: Zero reserved fields
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with request_ptr, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with request_ptr, 48, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with request_ptr, 56, 0

    Note: Advance tail (circular)
    Set tail to (tail plus 1) modulo by capacity
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx, 48, tail

    Note: Increment size
    Set size to size plus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx, 32, size

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Dequeuing removes and returns the next instantiation request from the queue.
Returns null if queue is empty.
@End Reasoning

Process called "dequeue_instantiation_request" takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let work_queue be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 16
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 24
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 32
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 40

    Note: Check if queue is empty
    If size is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Calculate head position
    Let request_offset be head multiplied by 64
    Let request_ptr be work_queue plus request_offset

    Note: Allocate request structure for return
    Let returned_request be proc allocate from Layout with 64
    proc memory_copy from Memory with returned_request, request_ptr, 64

    Note: Advance head (circular)
    Set head to (head plus 1) modulo by capacity
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx, 40, head

    Note: Decrement size
    Set size to size minus 1
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx, 32, size

    Return returned_request
End Process

@Reasoning
Growing the work queue doubles its capacity and copies all existing requests
to the new larger queue. This happens automatically when the queue fills.
@End Reasoning

Process called "grow_work_queue" takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let old_queue be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 16
    Let old_capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 24
    Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 32
    Let head be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 40

    Note: Double capacity
    Let new_capacity be old_capacity multiplied by 2
    Let new_queue_size be new_capacity multiplied by 64
    Let new_queue be proc allocate from Layout with new_queue_size

    Note: Copy all elements from old queue to new queue (linearize circular buffer)
    Let dst_idx be 0
    Let src_idx be head

    While dst_idx is less than size:
        Let src_offset be src_idx multiplied by 64
        Let dst_offset be dst_idx multiplied by 64

        Let src_ptr be old_queue plus src_offset
        Let dst_ptr be new_queue plus dst_offset

        proc memory_copy from Memory with dst_ptr, src_ptr, 64

        Set src_idx to (src_idx plus 1) modulo by old_capacity
        Set dst_idx to dst_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Free old queue
    proc deallocate from Layout with old_queue

    Note: Update context
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx, 16, new_queue
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx, 24, new_capacity
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx, 48, size

    Return 1
End Process

Note:
========================================
MAIN MONOMORPHIZATION DRIVER
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
The main monomorphization driver orchestrates the entire process:
1. Analyze HIR to find all generic call sites
2. Queue instantiation requests for each call site
3. Process work queue until empty
4. Return monomorphized HIR

This is the entry point for monomorphization of a compilation unit.
@End Reasoning

Process called "monomorphize_compilation_unit" takes hir as Integer, compilation_unit_id as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Create monomorphization context
    Let ctx be proc create_monomorphization_context with compilation_unit_id

    Note: Analyze HIR to discover all generic call sites
    proc discover_generic_call_sites with ctx, hir

    Note: Process work queue until empty
    proc process_work_queue with ctx

    Note: Build monomorphized HIR with all instantiated definitions and rewritten call sites
    Let result be proc build_monomorphized_hir with ctx, hir

    Note: Destroy context
    proc destroy_monomorphization_context with ctx

    Return result
End Process

@Reasoning
Processing the work queue is the core loop of monomorphization. It:
1. Dequeues the next instantiation request
2. Instantiates the generic definition
3. Analyzes the instantiated code for new generic calls
4. Queues any newly discovered instantiations
5. Repeats until queue is empty

This handles transitive dependencies - instantiating A<Integer> might require
instantiating B<String> which might require C<Float>, etc.
@End Reasoning

Process called "process_work_queue" takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Let iteration_count be 0

    Note: Process until work queue is empty
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Note: Get next request
        Let request be proc dequeue_instantiation_request with ctx

        If request is equal to 0:
            Note: Queue is empty - done
            Return iteration_count
        End If

        Note: Extract request fields
        Let generic_def be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with request, 0
        Let type_args be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with request, 8
        Let type_arg_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with request, 16
        Let call_site be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with request, 24

        Note: Perform instantiation
        Let inst_ctx be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 8
        Let instantiated_def be proc instantiate_generic from GenericInst with inst_ctx, generic_def, type_args, type_arg_count

        Note: If instantiation succeeded, store mapping and analyze for new generic calls
        If instantiated_def is not equal to 0:
            Note: Add instantiated definition to list
            Let instantiated_defs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 72
            proc append from List with instantiated_defs, instantiated_def

            Note: Map call site to instantiated definition
            If call_site is not equal to 0:
                Let call_site_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 80
                proc hashtable_set from HashTable with call_site_map, call_site, instantiated_def
            End If

            Note: Analyze instantiated definition for new generic calls
            proc discover_generic_calls_in_definition with ctx, instantiated_def

            Note: Increment processed count
            Let processed be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 56
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with ctx, 56, (processed plus 1)
        End If

        Note: Free request structure
        proc deallocate from Layout with request

        Set iteration_count to iteration_count plus 1
    End While

    Return iteration_count
End Process

Note:
========================================
GENERIC CALL SITE DISCOVERY
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
Discovering generic call sites analyzes HIR to find all uses of generic
types and functions. For each use, we queue an instantiation request with
the concrete type arguments.

This is a recursive tree traversal that examines expressions, type references,
and calls.
@End Reasoning

Process called "discover_generic_call_sites" takes ctx as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get HIR module structure
    Let module_count_offset be 8
    Let modules_offset be 16
    Let module_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hir, module_count_offset
    Let modules be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hir, modules_offset

    Note: Analyze each module
    Let module_idx be 0
    While module_idx is less than module_count:
        Let module_ptr_offset be module_idx multiplied by 8
        Let module be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with modules, module_ptr_offset

        If module is not equal to 0:
            proc discover_calls_in_module with ctx, module
        End If

        Set module_idx to module_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "discover_calls_in_module" takes ctx as Integer, module as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get module functions
    Let func_count_offset be 16
    Let funcs_offset be 24
    Let func_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with module, func_count_offset
    Let funcs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with module, funcs_offset

    Note: Analyze each function
    Let func_idx be 0
    While func_idx is less than func_count:
        Let func_ptr_offset be func_idx multiplied by 8
        Let func be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with funcs, func_ptr_offset

        If func is not equal to 0:
            proc discover_generic_calls_in_definition with ctx, func
        End If

        Set func_idx to func_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Get module types
    Let type_count_offset be 32
    Let types_offset be 40
    Let type_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with module, type_count_offset
    Let types be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with module, types_offset

    Note: Analyze each type
    Let type_idx be 0
    While type_idx is less than type_count:
        Let type_ptr_offset be type_idx multiplied by 8
        Let type_def be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with types, type_ptr_offset

        If type_def is not equal to 0:
            proc discover_calls_in_type_def with ctx, type_def
        End If

        Set type_idx to type_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "discover_generic_calls_in_definition" takes ctx as Integer, definition as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get definition kind
    Let kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with definition, 0

    If kind is equal to 1:  Note: PROCESS_DEF
        Note: Analyze process body for generic calls
        Let body_offset be 48
        Let body be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with definition, body_offset
        If body is not equal to 0:
            proc discover_calls_in_statement with ctx, body
        End If
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "discover_calls_in_type_def" takes ctx as Integer, type_def as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Analyze type methods
    Let method_count_offset be 48
    Let methods_offset be 56
    Let method_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_def, method_count_offset
    Let methods be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with type_def, methods_offset

    Let method_idx be 0
    While method_idx is less than method_count:
        Let method_ptr_offset be method_idx multiplied by 8
        Let method be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with methods, method_ptr_offset
        If method is not equal to 0:
            proc discover_generic_calls_in_definition with ctx, method
        End If
        Set method_idx to method_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "discover_calls_in_statement" takes ctx as Integer, stmt as Integer returns Integer:
    If stmt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get statement kind
    Let stmt_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, 0

    If stmt_kind is equal to 1:  Note: LET_BINDING
        Let value_offset be 24
        Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, value_offset
        proc discover_calls_in_expression with ctx, value
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 2:  Note: RETURN
        Set value_offset to 16
        Set value to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, value_offset
        proc discover_calls_in_expression with ctx, value
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 3:  Note: IF
        Let condition_offset be 16
        Let then_offset be 24
        Let else_offset be 32
        Let condition be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, condition_offset
        Let then_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, then_offset
        Let else_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, else_offset

        proc discover_calls_in_expression with ctx, condition
        proc discover_calls_in_statement with ctx, then_stmt
        If else_stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc discover_calls_in_statement with ctx, else_stmt
        End If
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 4:  Note: WHILE
        Set condition_offset to 16
        Let body_offset be 24
        Set condition to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, condition_offset
        Let body be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, body_offset

        proc discover_calls_in_expression with ctx, condition
        proc discover_calls_in_statement with ctx, body
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 5:  Note: BLOCK
        Let stmt_count_offset be 16
        Let stmts_offset be 24
        Let stmt_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, stmt_count_offset
        Let stmts be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, stmts_offset

        Let stmt_idx be 0
        While stmt_idx is less than stmt_count:
            Let stmt_ptr_offset be stmt_idx multiplied by 8
            Let inner_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmts, stmt_ptr_offset
            proc discover_calls_in_statement with ctx, inner_stmt
            Set stmt_idx to stmt_idx plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Process called "discover_calls_in_expression" takes ctx as Integer, expr as Integer returns Integer:
    If expr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get expression kind
    Let expr_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, 0

    If expr_kind is equal to 1:  Note: BINARY_OP
        Let left_offset be 24
        Let right_offset be 32
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, left_offset
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, right_offset
        proc discover_calls_in_expression with ctx, left
        proc discover_calls_in_expression with ctx, right
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 2:  Note: UNARY_OP
        Let operand_offset be 24
        Let operand be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, operand_offset
        proc discover_calls_in_expression with ctx, operand
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 3:  Note: CALL
        Note: Check if this is a generic call
        Let callee_offset be 24
        Let type_args_offset be 32
        Let arg_count_offset be 40
        Let callee be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, callee_offset
        Let args be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, type_args_offset
        Let arg_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, arg_count_offset

        Note: Check if callee is generic
        Let is_generic be proc is_generic_definition with callee
        If is_generic is equal to 1:
            Note: Extract type arguments from call site
            Let call_type_args be proc extract_type_arguments_from_call with expr
            Let call_type_arg_count be proc get_type_argument_count with expr

            If call_type_args is not equal to 0:
                Note: Queue instantiation request
                proc enqueue_instantiation_request with ctx, callee, call_type_args, call_type_arg_count, expr
            End If
        End If

        Note: Recursively analyze arguments
        Let arg_idx be 0
        While arg_idx is less than arg_count:
            Let arg_ptr_offset be arg_idx multiplied by 8
            Let arg be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with args, arg_ptr_offset
            proc discover_calls_in_expression with ctx, arg
            Set arg_idx to arg_idx plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

Note:
========================================
UTILITIES
========================================
:End Note

Process called "is_generic_definition" takes definition as Integer returns Integer:
    If definition is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Check if definition has generic parameters
    Let param_count_offset be 48
    Let param_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with definition, param_count_offset

    If param_count is greater than 0:
        Return 1
    End If

    Return 0
End Process

Process called "extract_type_arguments_from_call" takes call_expr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get type arguments from call expression
    Let type_args_offset be 48
    Let type_args be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with call_expr, type_args_offset
    Return type_args
End Process

Process called "get_type_argument_count" takes call_expr as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get type argument count from call expression
    Let type_arg_count_offset be 56
    Let type_arg_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with call_expr, type_arg_count_offset
    Return type_arg_count
End Process

Note:
========================================
STATISTICS COLLECTION
========================================
:End Note

Process called "get_monomorphization_statistics" takes ctx as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Allocate statistics structure (64 bytes)
    Let stats be proc allocate from Layout with 64

    Note: Get cache statistics
    Let cache be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 0
    Let hit_count_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    Let miss_count_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    Let entry_count_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    Let eviction_count_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    Let collision_count_ptr be proc allocate from Layout with 8

    proc cache_get_statistics from Cache with cache, hit_count_ptr, miss_count_ptr, entry_count_ptr, eviction_count_ptr, collision_count_ptr

    Let hit_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with hit_count_ptr, 0
    Let entry_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with entry_count_ptr, 0

    Note: Fill statistics
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with stats, 0, entry_count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with stats, 8, hit_count
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with stats, 16, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with stats, 24, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with stats, 32, 0

    Note: Zero reserved
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with stats, 40, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with stats, 48, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with stats, 56, 0

    Note: Free temporary pointers
    proc deallocate from Layout with hit_count_ptr
    proc deallocate from Layout with miss_count_ptr
    proc deallocate from Layout with entry_count_ptr
    proc deallocate from Layout with eviction_count_ptr
    proc deallocate from Layout with collision_count_ptr

    Return stats
End Process

Note:
========================================
HIR RECONSTRUCTION
========================================
:End Note

@Reasoning
Building the monomorphized HIR creates a new HIR tree with:
1. All monomorphized function definitions added to the module
2. All generic call sites rewritten to call monomorphized versions

This transforms the generic HIR into a fully concrete, monomorphized HIR
ready for lowering to MIR.

The process:
1. Get all instantiated definitions from context
2. Add them to the first module's function list (expanded capacity as needed)
3. Walk all statements/expressions and rewrite call sites using the call_site_mapping
@End Reasoning

Process called "build_monomorphized_hir" takes ctx as Integer, original_hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get instantiated definitions list
    Let instantiated_defs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 72
    Let instantiated_count be proc size from List with instantiated_defs

    Note: Get call site mapping
    Let call_site_map be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with ctx, 80

    Note: If no instantiations occurred, return original HIR
    If instantiated_count is equal to 0:
        Return original_hir
    End If

    Note: Get HIR structure (module_count at offset 8, modules at offset 16)
    Let module_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with original_hir, 8
    Let modules_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with original_hir, 16

    Note: Get first module (assumption: single module for now)
    If module_count is equal to 0:
        Display "Warning: No modules in HIR during monomorphization"
        Return original_hir
    End If

    Let first_module be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with modules_ptr, 0

    Note: Get module's function list (func_count at offset 16, funcs at offset 24)
    Let func_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with first_module, 16
    Let funcs_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with first_module, 24

    Note: Create new expanded function array (original + instantiated)
    Let new_func_count be func_count plus instantiated_count
    Let new_funcs_size be new_func_count multiplied by 8
    Let new_funcs be proc allocate from Layout with new_funcs_size

    Note: Copy original functions to new array
    Let copy_size be func_count multiplied by 8
    proc memory_copy from Memory with new_funcs, funcs_ptr, copy_size

    Note: Append instantiated definitions
    Let inst_idx be 0
    While inst_idx is less than instantiated_count:
        Let instantiated_def be proc get from List with instantiated_defs, inst_idx
        Let target_offset be (func_count plus inst_idx) multiplied by 8
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with new_funcs, target_offset, instantiated_def
        Set inst_idx to inst_idx plus 1
    End While

    Note: Update module with new function array
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with first_module, 16, new_func_count
    proc deallocate from Layout with funcs_ptr
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with first_module, 24, new_funcs

    Note: Rewrite all call sites in the HIR to use monomorphized versions
    proc rewrite_call_sites_in_module with first_module, call_site_map

    Return original_hir
End Process

@Reasoning
Rewriting call sites walks the entire HIR module and for each call expression,
checks if it's in the call_site_mapping. If so, replaces the callee with the
monomorphized version.

This ensures all generic calls are replaced with calls to concrete instantiations.
@End Reasoning

Process called "rewrite_call_sites_in_module" takes module as Integer, call_site_map as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Get module functions (func_count at offset 16, funcs at offset 24)
    Let func_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with module, 16
    Let funcs be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with module, 24

    Note: Rewrite call sites in each function
    Let func_idx be 0
    While func_idx is less than func_count:
        Let func_ptr_offset be func_idx multiplied by 8
        Let func be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with funcs, func_ptr_offset

        If func is not equal to 0:
            Note: Get function body (body at offset 48)
            Let body_offset be 48
            Let body be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with func, body_offset

            If body is not equal to 0:
                proc rewrite_call_sites_in_statement with body, call_site_map
            End If
        End If

        Set func_idx to func_idx plus 1
    End While

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Recursively walks statements to find and rewrite call expressions.
For each statement type, recursively processes nested statements and expressions.
@End Reasoning

Process called "rewrite_call_sites_in_statement" takes stmt as Integer, call_site_map as Integer returns Integer:
    If stmt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get statement kind (at offset 0)
    Let stmt_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, 0

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11000:  Note: LET_BINDING
        Let value_offset be 24
        Let value be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, value_offset
        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with value, call_site_map
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11010:  Note: RETURN
        Set value_offset to 16
        Set value to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, value_offset
        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with value, call_site_map
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11003:  Note: IF
        Let condition_offset be 16
        Let then_offset be 24
        Let else_offset be 32
        Let condition be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, condition_offset
        Let then_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, then_offset
        Let else_stmt be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, else_offset

        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with condition, call_site_map
        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_statement with then_stmt, call_site_map
        If else_stmt is not equal to 0:
            proc rewrite_call_sites_in_statement with else_stmt, call_site_map
        End If
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11008:  Note: WHILE
        Set condition_offset to 16
        Let body_offset be 24
        Set condition to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, condition_offset
        Let body be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, body_offset

        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with condition, call_site_map
        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_statement with body, call_site_map
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11007:  Note: FOR
        Let iterable_offset be 24
        Set body_offset to 32
        Let iterable be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, iterable_offset
        Set body to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, body_offset

        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with iterable, call_site_map
        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_statement with body, call_site_map
    End If

    If stmt_kind is equal to 11018:  Note: BLOCK_STATEMENT
        Note: Block contains list of child statements
        Let children_offset be 24
        Let children be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, children_offset
        Let child_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with stmt, 32

        Let child_idx be 0
        While child_idx is less than child_count:
            Let child_offset be child_idx multiplied by 8
            Let child be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with children, child_offset
            proc rewrite_call_sites_in_statement with child, call_site_map
            Set child_idx to child_idx plus 1
        End While
    End If

    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Recursively walks expressions to find call expressions that need rewriting.
When a call expression is found, checks if it's in the call_site_mapping.
If mapped, replaces the callee with the monomorphized function.
@End Reasoning

Process called "rewrite_call_sites_in_expression" takes expr as Integer, call_site_map as Integer returns Integer:
    If expr is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get expression kind (at offset 0)
    Let expr_kind be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, 0

    If expr_kind is equal to 10005:  Note: CALL_EXPRESSION
        Note: Check if this call site has a monomorphized target
        Let monomorphized_def be proc hashtable_get from HashTable with call_site_map, expr

        If monomorphized_def is not equal to 0:
            Note: Replace callee with monomorphized function (callee at offset 8 in HIRCallExpression)
            Note: Using offset 24 based on HIRNode base (96 bytes) then HIRCallExpression callee field
            Let callee_offset be 24
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with expr, callee_offset, monomorphized_def
        End If

        Note: Recursively process arguments
        Let args_offset be 32
        Let arg_count_offset be 40
        Let args be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, args_offset
        Let arg_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, arg_count_offset

        Let arg_idx be 0
        While arg_idx is less than arg_count:
            Let arg_offset be arg_idx multiplied by 8
            Let arg be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with args, arg_offset
            proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with arg, call_site_map
            Set arg_idx to arg_idx plus 1
        End While
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10002:  Note: BINARY_EXPRESSION
        Let left_offset be 16
        Let right_offset be 24
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, left_offset
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, right_offset

        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with left, call_site_map
        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with right, call_site_map
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10003:  Note: UNARY_EXPRESSION
        Let operand_offset be 16
        Let operand be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, operand_offset
        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with operand, call_site_map
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10007:  Note: MEMBER_EXPRESSION
        Let object_offset be 8
        Let object be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, object_offset
        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with object, call_site_map
    End If

    If expr_kind is equal to 10006:  Note: INDEX_EXPRESSION
        Set object_offset to 8
        Let index_offset be 16
        Set object to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, object_offset
        Let index be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with expr, index_offset

        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with object, call_site_map
        proc rewrite_call_sites_in_expression with index, call_site_map
    End If

    Return 1
End Process
